## PHASE 4 — Migration Wave Planner

`src/lib/glance/wave-planner.ts`

Input: the dependency graph (directed acyclic graph, or DAG approximation)

Algorithm: topological sort with criticality weighting

```
Wave 1 — Leaf nodes (no incoming critical dependencies)
  - S3 buckets (data storage, no incoming edges from other services)
  - Route 53 DNS records
  - IAM roles / KMS keys / Secrets (infrastructure primitives)
  - SQS queues (consumers depend on them, not vice versa)

Wave 2 — Services that only depend on Wave 1 resources
  - Databases (RDS, ElastiCache, DynamoDB) — depend only on VPC + secrets
  - ECR repositories

Wave 3 — Compute services that depend on Wave 2
  - Lambda functions (depend on databases, SQS, S3)
  - ECS services (depend on databases, ECR, secrets)
  - EKS cluster (depends on ECR, databases)

Wave 4 — Traffic routing (depends on compute being live)
  - ALB / NLB
  - CloudFront (if applicable → replace with EU CDN)
  - API Gateway (depends on Lambda)

Wave 5 — Supporting services (can migrate last)
  - CloudWatch log groups → target cloud logging
  - IAM users / cross-account roles
  - SSM Parameter Store
```

Output per wave:
- Ordered list of resources
- Estimated migration effort (low/medium/high) per resource
- Blockers: "do not migrate this until wave N is complete"
- EU cloud recommendation: best-fit from Lens analysis for this resource type

