## PHASE 5 — Visualisation

### 5.1 — Architecture Graph

Technology: React + `@xyflow/react` (React Flow) — excellent for node/edge graphs,
well-maintained, used in production by major tools.

Layout algorithm: `dagre` (hierarchical layout) or ELK.js for large graphs.

Nodes:
- Icon = service type (EC2 server icon, RDS database icon, Lambda function icon, etc.)
- Color = migration status (grey = not started, blue = planned, amber = in progress, green = migrated)
- Border = criticality (red border = high, no border = low)
- Label = resource name
- Click → resource detail panel (right sidebar)

Edges:
- Solid line = confirmed dependency
- Dashed line = inferred dependency
- Color = dependency type (blue = network, purple = IAM, green = data, orange = event)
- Label = dependency type on hover
- Arrow direction = data/control flow direction

Controls:
- Filter by service type (show only databases + their consumers)
- Filter by VPC / subnet
- Filter by migration wave (show only wave 2)
- Group by: service type / VPC / tag / migration wave
- Zoom to fit / zoom to selection
- Fullscreen mode

### 5.2 — Migration Wave View

Alternative to the graph: a swimlane view grouped by wave.

Wave 1 | Wave 2 | Wave 3 | Wave 4 | Wave 5
[S3]   | [RDS]  | [Lambda] | [ALB] | [CloudWatch]
[SQS]  | [ECR]  | [ECS]    | [CF]  | [IAM]
       |        | [EKS]    |       |

Click any resource → detail panel.
Drag resource between waves → override wave assignment (with warning if it breaks dependency order).

### 5.3 — Resource Detail Panel

Right-side panel, appears on resource click:
- Resource name, type, ID, region
- Configuration summary (key fields, no secrets)
- Compliance flags from Lens compliance engine
- Incoming dependencies (what depends on this resource)
- Outgoing dependencies (what this resource depends on)
- Migration status (not started / planned / in progress / complete)
- Lens compatibility: compatible/partial/none for each target EU cloud
- Button: "Add to Guide blueprint" → triggers blueprint generation for this resource

