## PHASE 6 — Change Detection

### 6.1 — Drift Detection

On every re-scan, compare to the previous snapshot:

NEW resources:
- "14 new resources detected since last scan"
- Immediately check: do any new resources break the dependency graph or create new compliance flags?
- Alert if: new resource has a critical compliance flag (e.g., new Rekognition collection)

REMOVED resources:
- "3 resources decommissioned since last scan"
- Check: were any of these resources dependencies for other resources?
- Alert if: a critical dependency was removed (may indicate a production issue)

NEW dependencies:
- "New connection detected: Lambda prod-auth → RDS prod-db (event source mapping)"
- This changes the migration wave plan — surface immediately

CHANGED configuration:
- Security group rule changes, IAM policy changes, new environment variables
- These can change the dependency graph without adding/removing resources

### 6.2 — Architecture Snapshots

Users can name and save snapshots:
- "Before migration - April 2026"
- "Post-Lambda removal"
- "Hybrid state (wave 1-2 on Hetzner)"

Snapshots are immutable. Users can diff two snapshots:
- Side-by-side graph view (red = in A only, green = in B only, grey = in both)
- Summary: "47 resources added, 12 removed, 8 connection changes"

